{"id":1248,"date":"2014-06-03T08:03:33","date_gmt":"2014-06-03T05:03:33","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/?p=1248"},"modified":"2014-06-03T21:27:26","modified_gmt":"2014-06-03T18:27:26","slug":"ramadan-2014-fundraising","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/ramadan-2014-fundraising\/","title":{"rendered":"Ramadan 2014 &#8211; Fundraising"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/07\/mini-20120719_140126.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-538\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/07\/mini-20120719_140126-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"Ramadan Food Distribution\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/07\/mini-20120719_140126-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/07\/mini-20120719_140126-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2012\/07\/mini-20120719_140126.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a>QWT is now fundraising for its annual Ramadan food distribution project. This year we are targeting to feed 1,000 poor Zakat eligible families across Pakistan. The cost of feeding a family of 4-5 members is $62 (KD 17.50; Rs 6,000). Each family will be provided with a approximately 50kg of un-cooked food stables including 20kg of flour, 10kg of rice, 5kg of sugar, 5kg of lentils, 2.5kg of chickpeas, 2.5kg of oil, 2.5kg of ghee, 2kg of gram flour, 1kg of dates, 0.5kg of tea and mix spices.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">QWT has been organizing Ramadan food distribution for the past six years. Last year we distributed 76.1 tons of food, to more than 1,000 families (<a title=\"Ramadan 2013 \" href=\"http:\/\/10.0.0.56\/?p=925\" target=\"_blank\">details<\/a>).<\/p>\n<h2>Project Summary<\/h2>\n<p><strong>Fundraising Period:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>June 1 to June 20 2014<\/p>\n<p><strong>Beneficiaries:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>1,000 families and approximately 5,000 children &amp; adults, in Pakistan.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Project Execution:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Food will be distributed between June 24-28 in collaboration with various partner organizations like Muslim Aid, READ Foundation and Almustafa Development Network. The beneficiaries will be\u00a0pre-screened prior to the distribution and all efforts will be made to ensure they are Zakat eligible.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Why Pakistan:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Poverty is widespread in Pakistan and is particularly predominant in rural areas. Nearly two thirds of the population, and 80 per cent of the country\u2019s poor people, live in rural parts of the country. Studies on poverty show that every third Pakistani is living his life below the poverty line. About 58.7 million out of 180 million Pakistanis are living below the poverty line.<a href=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/Tharparkar2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-1122\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/Tharparkar2-300x155.jpg\" alt=\"Tharparkar\" width=\"300\" height=\"155\" srcset=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/Tharparkar2-300x155.jpg 300w, https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/Tharparkar2.jpg 580w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">According to the Human Development Index, 60.3% of Pakistan&#8217;s population lives on under $2 a day, and some 22.6% live under $1 a day. Wealth distribution in Pakistan is highly uneven, with the top 10% of the population earning 27.6% and the bottom 10% earning only 4.1% of the income. According to the United Nations Human Development Report, Pakistan&#8217;s human development indicators, especially those for women, fall significantly below those of countries with comparable levels of per-capita income.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>Donate Online<\/h2>\n<figure id=\"attachment_1080\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1080\" style=\"width: 170px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a title=\"Ramadan Food Distribution\" href=\"https:\/\/uk.virginmoneygiving.com\/fundraiser-web\/donate\/makeDonationForFundraiserDisplay.action?fundraiserActivityId=443249\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-1080\" src=\"https:\/\/qidwaiwelfare.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/04\/478678683c.jpg\" alt=\"Ramadan Food Distribution\" width=\"170\" height=\"125\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1080\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Ramadan Food Distribution<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Online donations will be made in British Pounds, and \u00a31.00 = $1.67, and \u00a31.00 = KD 0.475.<\/p>\n<h2>Donate via bank wire transfer<\/h2>\n<h3><strong>Pakistan<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><strong>Account Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Qidwai Welfare Trust<\/p>\n<p><strong>Account Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a00055001586000087<\/p>\n<p><strong>IBAN Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0PK93BURJ0055001586000087<\/p>\n<p><strong>Bank Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Burj Bank Ltd.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Address &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0F8 Markaz Branch, Islamabad, Pakistan<\/p>\n<p><strong>Swift Code &#8211;\u00a0<\/strong>BURJPKKAXXX<\/p>\n<p><strong>Currency &#8211;\u00a0<\/strong>Pakistani Rupee<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><strong>United Kingdom\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><strong>Account Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0The Charity Network<\/p>\n<p><strong>Account Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a021050953<\/p>\n<p><strong>IBAN Number &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0GB77NWBK54210721050953<\/p>\n<p><strong>Bank Name &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Natwest Bank<\/p>\n<p><strong>Address &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Basford Branch, 536 Valley Road, Nottingham\u00a0NG5 1JJ, UK<\/p>\n<p><strong>Swift C